text: Jorge Campos (born September 19, 1991 in Havana) is a Cuban table tennis player. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the men's singles event, in which he was eliminated in the first round by Eugene Wang. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Cuban male table tennis players Category:Olympic table tennis players of Cuba Category:Table tennis players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Pan American Games medalists in table tennis Category:Pan American Games bronze medalists for Cuba Category:Table tennis players at the 2011 Pan American Games Category:Table tennis players at the 2019 Pan American Games Category:Table tennis players at the 2015 Pan American Games
